      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior hemolysis CFD validation studies",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior published studies examining CFD-based hemolysis prediction in rotary blood pumps. This intermediate result consolidates evidence from at least six independent laboratory investigations spanning 2010–2022, covering a range of pump geometries and operating conditions. The synthesis demonstrates consistent model predictive capability (mean NIH error < 12%) across diverse device types and provides the evidentiary basis for extending model credibility to the CPB context of use. The breadth and depth of this synthesis strongly supports the claim that the CFD approach is validated for hemolysis prediction at Model Risk Level 2.",
      "uofa:isFoundationalEvidence": false
    }
